d Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":22,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William Deincourt was born in 1268, in Ottery St Mary, Devon, England. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs William Deincourt. He died on 24 June 1314, in Bannockburn, Stirlingshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 46."},"et":{"1268–24 June 1314":"1268–24. juuni 1314","1272–Female":"1272–Surnud","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1268–1314":"1268–1314","24 June 1314":"24. juuni 1314","1314":"1314","1268":"1268","1300":"1300","1272":"1272","1290":"1290","killed at the Battle of Bannockburn stirlingshire scotland":"Bannockburn, Stirlingshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Ottery St Mary, Devon, England":"Ottery St Mary, Devon, England","Mendlesham, Suffolk, England":"Mendlesham, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1268–24 June 1314":"1268–24. kesäkuuta 1314","1272–Female":"1272–Kuollut","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1268–1314":"1268–1314","24 June 1314":"24. kesäkuuta 1314","1314":"1314","1268":"1268","1300":"1300","1272":"1272","1290":"1290","killed at the Battle of Bannockburn stirlingshire scotland":"Bannockburn, Stirlingshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskun